== Radio

Radio is a intranet based recorder for audio streams. It has been developed
for demonstration purposes of the Ruby on Rails framework.

Radio is copyright (c) 2006-2007 GL Networks <http://www.glnetworks.de/>,
Martin Rehfeld <martin.rehfeld@glnetworks.de>

Radio is licensed under the terms of the GNU General Public License (GPL),
version 2.0 or later, as published by the Free Software Foundation.  See
the file COPYING [included] or <http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.txt> for
the terms of the latest version of the GNU General Public License.

Radio comes with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY, to the extent permitted by
applicable law.

Check <http://www.glnetworks.de/rails_project> for updates.

=== Model Documentation

* Recorder (threaded recording and convertion to MP3 using Mplayer and LAME)

* Station (define radio stations as recording sources)

* Recording (keep track of Recordings and their state)

=== Controller Documentation

* RecordingsController (main user GUI)

* StationsController   (scaffolded admin GUI for radio stations)

